  "text": "Using Theorem 1.4, we obtain an almost optimal fractional solution (y, z) of LP relaxation in Equations (6)- (10) of IP in Equations (13)- [CITATION_1] . We apply randomized rounding in order to select a path for each demand. Specifically, for each demand i ∈ D, we consider the standard flow decomposition into paths: In the decomposition, each path p connecting s i to t i has a weight λ i,p ∈ R + . For every edge e, p:e ∈p λ i,p = d i y i,e ; and p λ i,p = d i . For each i, the approximation algorithm picks one path p connecting s i to t i at random with probability λ i,p /d i and routes all demands from s i to p i via p. Thus, the algorithm always obtains a feasible solution.",
